Ah, gotcha - I think @Victor Zeng and @Anilâ€™s PR yesterday was still using the temporary builder label I spun up for testing, and I didn't see that when I merged it. The new label was constrained to a much smaller instance cap, so everyone was waiting for a small pool :slightly_smiling_face:

Fixed it on the Jenkins side for now, just allowing the old pool to pick up either label, so the capacity is back to normal. :+1:

Thank you! Already CIs for my PRs moving forward :raised_hands:
Oops, sorry Victor, I missed a step it seems :slightly_smiling_face: I've merged the label update, sorry I got my wires crossed!
